Exception Summary
AuthenticationException this exception is thrown when an incorrect username and/or password is supplied to a LowLevelCommunicator.
FailedResponseException  
ProtocolMismatchException A ProtocolMismatchException is thrown when the client sends information not conforming to the OpenGroove protocol, indicating that they're using the wrong type of client (for example, using a web browser) to connect to the OpenGroove server, or that they have the wrong security key.
